# PR branch workflow

## Binding rule

Agents must not commit implementation work directly on the default branch unless
the user explicitly authorizes that in the same request.

## Start of work

```bash
git fetch origin
bash scripts/git/prepare-work-branch.sh <topic-slug>
```

Use a short, descriptive topic slug. The script creates or resets
`cursor/<topic-slug>` from the remote default branch.

## Finish of work

1. Run the relevant checks.
2. Commit on the PR branch.
3. Push the branch.
4. Open or update a PR into the default branch.
5. Tell the user: `PR: <link>. Merge PR #N to ship.`

## Break-glass direct default branch

Allowed only when the user explicitly says so in the same request. Requirements:

- Include `[direct-main]` in the commit message.
- Prefer the smallest safe change.
- Explain why PR flow was bypassed.

## Escalation block

```text
Blocked: I cannot safely complete this through the normal PR branch workflow.
Safe options:
A) Merge/open the PR branch.
B) Reply with explicit direct default-branch authorization and I will use [direct-main].
Needed from you: <specific action>.
```

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] Not on default branch.
- [ ] Branch is based on fresh origin default branch.
- [ ] PR exists or final response includes exact merge/open instruction.
